### Description

Currently we do a CredentialRequest like this ...

```
        Oid4vcCredentialRequest request = oauth.oid4vc()
                .credentialRequest()
                .endpoint(ctx.issuerMetadata.getCredentialEndpoint())
                .bearerToken(accessToken);

        if (credRequest.getCredentialConfigurationId() != null) {
            request.credentialConfigurationId(credRequest.getCredentialConfigurationId());
        }
        if (credRequest.getCredentialIdentifier() != null) {
            request.credentialIdentifier(credRequest.getCredentialIdentifier());
        }

        Oid4vcCredentialResponse credentialRequestResponse = request.send();
        int statusCode = credentialRequestResponse.getStatusCode();
        if (HttpStatus.SC_OK != statusCode) {
            throw new IllegalStateException(credentialRequestResponse.getErrorDescription() != null
                    ? credentialRequestResponse.getErrorDescription()
                    : "Request failed with status " + statusCode);
        }
```

This code has several issues ...

1. The caller already provides a valid `CredentialRequest`, which does not need to be copied into `Oid4vcCredentialRequest`
2. `Oid4vcCredentialRequest` extends `AbstractOid4vcRequest` which is (mostly) a duplicate of the already existing `AbstractHttpPostRequest`, which can be reused for the CredentialRequest like any other POST request.
3. This type of error handling (i.e. on unexpected http status) would need to be duplicated every time `Oid4vcCredentialResponse` is accessed. Instead it should be done in `Oid4vcCredentialResponse`

### Value Proposition

* Use the provided `CredentialRequest` directly in the HttpPostRequest
* Reuse logic in `AbstractHttpPostRequest` like any other POST Request
* Unify error handling across all OID4VCI requests using the OAuthClient API

### Goals

Cleaner and more reliable code

### Non-Goals

