When `InjectAdminClient` is used with `Mode.MANAGED_REALM`, there are two issues:

1) `@InjectAdminClient` has a `realmRef` attribute, but it's not used by the supplier

2) A client and user have to be defined in a `RealmConfig` class, or they won't be found. Example below:

Works:
```java
@KeycloakIntegrationTest
public class SomeTest {

    @InjectRealm(config = ConfigClass.class) // if `myClient` is in realm config, all is ok
    ManagedRealm realm;

    @InjectAdminClient(mode = MANAGED_REALM, client = "myClient")
    Keycloak keycloak;

    @Test
    public void test() { }

    private static class ConfigClass implements RealmConfig {
        @Override
        public RealmConfigBuilder configure(RealmConfigBuilder realm) {
            realm.addClient("myClient").secret("mySecret");
            return realm;
        }
    }
}
```

Doesn't work:
```java
@KeycloakIntegrationTest
public class SomeTest {

    @InjectRealm
    ManagedRealm realm;

    @InjectClient(config = ConfigClass.class) // `myClient` is defined outside realm config, can't find it
    ManagedClient client;

    @InjectAdminClient(mode = MANAGED_REALM, client = "myClient")
    Keycloak keycloak;

    @Test
    public void test() { }

    private static class ConfigClass implements ClientConfig {
        @Override
        public ClientConfigBuilder configure(ClientConfigBuilder client) {
            return client.clientId("myClient").secret("mySecret");
        }
    }
}
```
